      <bioghist id="aspace_d8cda379e26c6cd4a46db72117cbe6eb">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Paul Jablonski is a summer resident of Cherry Grove (Long Island), New York. He has been an active member of the lesbian, gay, bisexual, and transgender community there, organizing annual events such as the Cherry Grove LGBT Pride Parade and coordinating the Cherry Grove Chamber of Commerce.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_d304246a0155a26fa99517666225d982">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The collection comprises digital video files made from videotapes documenting the Cherry Bowl Volleyball Tournament, an annual charity beach volleyball tournament, begun in 1984, pitting the Cherry Grove Grovettes against various emergency services and police departments from the Long Island and New York City area.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_e6259f52901077f63525e51f395e1868">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The video file descriptions are arranged chronologically.</p>  
      </arrangement>
